{"pageProps":{"post":{"slug":"what-is-bash","id":"66e02c5a4d1d260001ae6435","uuid":"6d45f32a-816c-42e0-8f0b-90e7bcc965e5","title":"What is Bash?","html":"<p>Bash is a CLI that accepts and executes user commands in a text-based environment.</p><p>A sequence of these commands stored in a file is referred to as a Shell Script, which Bash is capable of reading and performing.</p><p><strong>Shell:</strong> software program or a command line interface that translates user instructions.</p><p>ðŸ’¡ Shell Scripts are interpreted and not compiled</p><h3 id=\"types-of-shell\">Types of Shell</h3><ol><li><strong>Bourne Shell (sh)</strong>: original Unix shell, simple and widely portable.</li><li><strong>Bourne Again Shell (bash)</strong>: default Linux shell with advanced scripting and customization.</li><li><strong>Korn Shell (ksh)</strong>: Combines features of Bourne and C shells, with advanced scripting.</li><li><strong>C Shell (csh)</strong>: shell with C-like syntax and command history, used for scripting and interactive use.</li><li><strong>Z Shell (zsh)</strong>: An advanced, customizable shell with powerful features and plugins.</li><li><strong>Fish Shell (fish)</strong>: user-friendly shell with modern features like syntax highlighting and autosuggestions.</li></ol><p>Step 1</p><p></p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-4.45.42-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-08-08 at 4.45.42â€¯PM.png\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1098\" height=\"402\" srcset=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/size/w600/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-4.45.42-PM.png 600w, http://localhost:2368/content/images/size/w1000/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-4.45.42-PM.png 1000w, http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-4.45.42-PM.png 1098w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><ul><li>Log in to the system, if itâ€™s a server</li><li>Open your terminal, if itâ€™s your computer</li></ul><p>If your prompt is not ending with <code><strong>$</strong></code>,type-<code>bash</code></p><p>To know shell types your operating system supports?:</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-4.52.30-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"694\" height=\"358\" srcset=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/size/w600/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-4.52.30-PM.png 600w, http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-4.52.30-PM.png 694w\"></figure><p>You will not be using above commands much, 90% of the time shell is used to navigate through folders and executing programs like&nbsp;<strong><code>ls</code></strong>,&nbsp;<strong><code>cd</code></strong>&nbsp;and other common commands.</p>","comment_id":"66c06b12d0323348cb7a51be","feature_image":"http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/09/Screenshot-2024-08-30-at-6.46.02-PM.png","featured":false,"visibility":"public","created_at":"2024-08-17T09:19:14.000+00:00","updated_at":"2024-09-04T09:48:36.000+00:00","published_at":"2024-08-17T09:23:20.000+00:00","custom_excerpt":"What is Bash; Types of Bash","codeinjection_head":null,"codeinjection_foot":null,"custom_template":null,"canonical_url":null,"url":"http://localhost:2368/what-is-bash/","excerpt":"What is Bash; Types of Bash","reading_time":1,"access":true,"comments":false,"og_image":null,"og_title":null,"og_description":null,"twitter_image":null,"twitter_title":null,"twitter_description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"email_subject":null,"frontmatter":null,"feature_image_alt":null,"feature_image_caption":null},"previous":null,"next":{"id":"66e02c5a4d1d260001ae6438","uuid":"adc51e98-2008-4a95-be60-92737a1bd337","title":"How to Write Your First Bash Scripts?","slug":"how-to-write-your-first-bash-scripts","html":"<p></p><p><strong>Bash Script:</strong> Simple text file that stores a series of commands, typically entered in the command line, to automate tasks in the Linux system.</p><h3 id=\"how-to-write-bash-scripts\"><strong>How to Write Bash Scripts?</strong></h3><p>Ensure you're in the desired directory by using <code>pwd</code> command and if not then change to desired directory using <code>cd</code> command</p><ol><li><strong>Create file with .sh extension:</strong></li></ol><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.03.49-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-08-08 at 5.30.00â€¯PM.png\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1104\" height=\"208\" srcset=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/size/w600/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.03.49-PM.png 600w, http://localhost:2368/content/images/size/w1000/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.03.49-PM.png 1000w, http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.03.49-PM.png 1104w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Execute the Script prefixing with <code>./file_name</code></p><ol start=\"2\"><li><strong>Open the script in text editor:</strong></li></ol><p><code>gedit apoo.sh</code></p><p>If gedit is not installed then run <code>brew install gedit</code></p><ol start=\"3\"><li><strong>Write down the bash script command within it:</strong></li></ol><p>ðŸ’¡ Every Bash script for Linux should start with the shebang line- \"#!/bin/bash\"</p><p>Letâ€™s start with the programming ritual- â€˜Hello Worldâ€™</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.29.03-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-08-08 at 5.29.03â€¯PM.png\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"650\" height=\"130\" srcset=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/size/w600/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.29.03-PM.png 600w, http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.29.03-PM.png 650w\"></figure><p>If you excecute this file now, it will give permission denied.</p><ol start=\"4\"><li><strong>Provide execution permission and execute it:</strong></li></ol><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.30.00-PM.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-08-08 at 5.03.49â€¯PM.png\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"824\" height=\"140\" srcset=\"http://localhost:2368/content/images/size/w600/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.30.00-PM.png 600w, http://localhost:2368/content/images/2024/08/Screenshot-2024-08-08-at-5.30.00-PM.png 824w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure>","comment_id":"66c06db5d0323348cb7a51f9","feature_image":null,"featured":false,"visibility":"public","created_at":"2024-08-17T09:30:29.000+00:00","updated_at":"2024-09-05T01:08:33.000+00:00","published_at":"2024-08-17T09:35:03.000+00:00","custom_excerpt":"How to create and excecute tour first bash script!!","codeinjection_head":"<script type=\"application/json\">\n  { \n  \"guide_name\":\"bash-guide\",\n  \"priority\": 1\n  }\n</script>","codeinjection_foot":null,"custom_template":null,"canonical_url":null,"tags":[{"id":"66e02c594d1d260001ae642a","name":"Bash","slug":"bash","description":null,"feature_image":null,"visibility":"public","og_image":null,"og_title":null,"og_description":null,"twitter_image":null,"twitter_title":null,"twitter_description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"codeinjection_head":null,"codeinjection_foot":null,"canonical_url":null,"accent_color":null,"url":"http://localhost:2368/tag/bash/"},{"id":"66e02c594d1d260001ae642e","name":"#Import 2024-09-10 11:24","slug":"hash-import-2024-09-10-11-24","description":null,"feature_image":null,"visibility":"internal","og_image":null,"og_title":null,"og_description":null,"twitter_image":null,"twitter_title":null,"twitter_description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"codeinjection_head":null,"codeinjection_foot":null,"canonical_url":null,"accent_color":null,"url":"http://localhost:2368/4